column5: Hey folks,  I know that you have seen this before but got playing with Movie Maker and was able to compile all of the videos that I have shot this weekend into one.  Just having fun     It turned out pretty good     Check it out and let me know what you think...    Leechman
Oh man that was unbelievable. Very nice construction for a home made lure I must say, I hope you make a video for those cranks. Thanks for sharing cheers.
great job sir!  Lovin the new style of fishing!  Keep up the good work, MTBF

That was great Jacques!!!  I should should try to make some videos sometime (then maybe Paul would believe I can catch 3 fish at one time!), I think you've inspired me!  Thanks for taking the time to put that together for us, I found it very entertaining!!!
Awesome job Jacques!!  Have you considered a job in film making?
Nice work bud, must feel good to catch fish on your own lures
Sweet stuff Leechman! You really got a good eye for design.
That's some cool creations you got there.... Great detail!

Thanks mojobass!!!  I'll see what I can do about that   Thanks Mike!!!   Thanks Glen... glad you liked it!!! and hope you make one.... would love to see you live in Bama   Thanks Tony!!!  May be I should   Thanks Fish4Eyes!!!  It sure does   Thanks Jet!!!  I'm trying   Thanks muskybugged!!!
Great job Jaques, you definitely have talent.  I have several ideas for lures but dont have a clue about how to get them made.
Thanks Don!!!  May be we could meet and talk about your ideas.... I'd be more than happy to help you out
Great job Jaques Totally enjoyed the vid.
Thanks Dan!!!  Was an absolute thrill to make
Windows movie maker!   A BIG congrats on a great video Sir.craftmen!   youv inspired me..... to hit lac lemay!

Thanks Kev!!!  Yes, Movie Maker, what a nice little program..... lots of options to make great videos Glad you liked it!!!  Leamy's got great potential.... I guess when the fish are active, they'll come out to play  Missed a heavy fish last time I was there     but I know it's still there.... will have to get busy in the area I was and see if I can catch it.  Thanks again Kevin!!!
